job_description:
We are looking for a Quality Control Associate Manager. Candidate will be located in Phnom Penh, Cambodia and will report directly to QC Manager.
Responsibilities include: 
- Analyze the quality inspection reports made by 3rd parties, deciding whether an order is authorized to be delivered or not.
- Find solutions and coordinate with different teams, in case of fail or pending result.
- Have a sense of supply chain and work closely with functional team of offices, in order to assure a product in excellent conditions, preventing delays on deliveries.
- Coordinate the operations in Quality department to make sure the good performance of inspections.
- Maintain updated the database for the office internal system and report any issues within them.
- Check, follow up & confirm potential new orders in system with responsible parties and coordinate upload.
- Manage, support on issues of suppliers interface related with quotations, schedules, forecasts.
- Support Quality team in other duties/projects
- Well-trained in Garment factory operation and manufacture.
- Familiar with all QC and manufacturing control documents.
- Able to identify problems and communicate with factories at all levels.
- Able to implement and drive QC training program in the manufacturing facilities.
- Lead with a “right first time” quality philosophy and practice.
- Attend PP meetings, support and assist in inline checking and final AQL inspections.
- Monitor the quality of the product through each of the various stages of production.
- Train newly hired quality personnel on company quality policies and how to use quality tools.
- Calibration and strengthening skills and judgement of QC team
- Lead Root Cause & CAP for any customer related quality issues
- Conduct factory evaluations on a regular basis with CAP follow up to address gaps
- Compilation of reports and analysis to guide management focus and actions.
- Other duties as assigned by Management.
Job Requirements:
- Based in Cambodia;
- Fluent in English is a MUST (oral & written); can speak Chinese is a big plus;
- At least 6-10 years of experience in QC fields;
- Willing to travel and out-station in provinces within Cambodia/Vietnam;
- Proven and well - established track record in managing quality for apparel products;
- Strong technical knowledge on quality matters (inspection levels, AQL, etc.); and fully versed and up to date with quality related best practices;
- Strong fabric and product knowledge, possess garment construction, pattern engineering and technical knowledge in 2D &3D software’s;
- Strong management, communication and interpersonal skills with internal team, liaison with our other offshore offices and with the customer;
- Excellent and comprehensive understanding of production requirements from a commercial and quality perspective;
- Good skill on time-managing, reporting and analyzing database;
- Analytical, detail focus, team-collaboration, and problem-solving skills;
- Proactive and autonomous, willing to learn and to perform under pressure in a fast-paced environment;
- Competent computer Skills, Experience in AX, Pivot 888 is a plus;
- Experience in conducting Classroom Training, in creating Workshop and Training modules an advantage.

Job Purpose
To process and analyze small business loan application by conducting credit investigations, scoring, credit checking and other underwriting activities in order to ensure good lending and loan quality of the branch as well as to coach, mentor and train less experienced Small Business Loan Officers and new comers to ensure all operational support and lending functions are accurately performed in accordance with the Bank’s small business loan policies as well as adhere to the government and NBC regulations.
Location
Preah Sihanouk Provincial Branch 
Major Areas of Responsibility
- Solicit both potentially existing and new clients in accordance with the guidelines stated in the small business loan policies and procedures to ensure the secured loans;
- On-board new small business loans to ensure delivery of disbursement target;
- Explain to clients the different types of loans and credit options that are available, as well as the terms of those services for further cross-selling;
- Collect all clients’ required documents for loan application to ensure their eligibility for having it approved;
- Conduct credit investigation to analyze applicants’ financial status, credit, property evaluations, repayment capacity to determine feasibility of granting loans;
- Gather valid applicants’ financial records by obtaining and compiling copies of clients’ credit histories, corporate financial statement and other financial information in order to prevent them from being conned;
- Conduct a site visit during loan assessment process to obtain in-depth information concerning to the purpose of customer’s loan application and ensure sufficient and acceptable loan security; 
- Make the regular site visits to existing customers in order to determine whether the loan should stay the same or be downgraded due to the actual condition of their loan collateral and/or financial situation as well as to develop relationship with customers for further cross-selling;
- Follow up delinquent client immediately and refer such case to the supervisor in order to proactively handle the branch loan portfolio; 
- Process registration of title deeds at local authority and land office to acquire the legal evidence of client’s ownership rights of the property;
- Stay abreast of new types of loans and other financial services and products to better meet customer needs;
- Handle complex customers’ issues whenever Small Business Loan Officers could not by remaining calm and executing the excellent customer service principles to find an amicable solution for all;
- Resolve team routine and complex issues to maintain productivities and morale;
- Act as a role model within the team to question, listen and give actionable feedback carefully in order to create a productive work atmosphere towards “speak up culture”.
Qualifications
- Bachelor’s degree in finance and banking, accounting or any relevant field;
- Minimum two years of working experiences in banking and financial services industry with a strong track record in granting loans.
- Excellent knowledge of the bank branch operations, rules and regulations, laws, granting loans, and credit risk management;
- Ability to use and communicate in both Khmer and English;
- Proficient Microsoft Office and Bank’s software;
- Good sales and customer services skills;
- Good math skills and ability to spot numerical errors;
- Good problem solving, negotiation and interpersonal skill;
- Strong dedication to accuracy and efficiency.

About AMRET
Job Summary 
Responsible for leading the development and delivery of accurate and insightful human resource reports and data analytics to support strategic decision-making, the role oversees the data collection, analysis, and interpretation of HR metrics related to workforce planning, headcount, turnover, diversity, compensation, and employee engagement, and serving as administrator to support and solve HR system issue.
Job Description
- Design and develop HR dashboard based on business needed; 
- Understand HR processes and able to recommend the HR reporting or dashboard that require for HR operation; 
- Ensure reports are used-friendly and accessible to relevant stakeholders by providing clear user guideline; 
- Improve dashboard functionality based on user feedback and evolving business needs; • Documented the data formula and maintain user access right of the related reports; 
- Perform as HCM administrator to manage the system functionalities and related administration part; 
- Collaborate with IT and HR process owner to improve system functionalities and data flow; 
- Report and raise the incident and/or change request by coordinate with IT and system vendor to provide issue resolution; 
- Manage & Documentation of HCM user manual/guide, user access right by closely work with process owner/IT security to stay up-to-date and comply with internal policy; 
- Validate HR data across systems to maintain consistency; 
- Update tool for personnel budget calculation based on the HC template and the change of benefits from time to time; 
- Prepare the calculation on personnel budget for mid-term and annual projection; 
-  Prepare the breakdown budget calculation by branch / department upon budget approval from management; 
- Monitor and analyse personnel cost projection vs actual expense, to ensure that the actual payment is align with the approval budget and/or additional approval; 
- Prepare regular or ad-hoc HR reports for Risk, Audit, lender, NBC and related team as timely manner; 
- Prepare related payroll report as assigned by manager; 
- Perform other tasks as assigned by line manager.  
Qualifications
- Degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, Data Analytics, Information Systems, or a related field; 
- Two years’ experience in HR operation which able to understand HR processes; 
- Two years of experience in HR reporting, HCM management, or data analysis within an HR ;
- Proficiency in Microsoft Excel, including advanced functions (pivot tables, VLOOKUP, Power Query, etc.);
- Strong command of Power BI for dashboard creation, data modelling, and visualization; 
- Experience in designing and developing dashboards using Power BI or similar data visualization tools.
